OL,3,CJersey to face rising energy bills in
OL,4,C2026
OL,6,F"Encouragingly, we're starting to see
OL,7,Fsigns of greater stability in
OL,8,Finternational energy markets which has
OL,9,Fhelped us keep this adjustment below
OL,10,Finflation."
OL,12,F"We've also been able to hold off
OL,13,Fbringing this 2.5% increase into
OL,14,Feffect until March 2026, so customers
OL,15,Fcan be assured it won't affect their
OL,16,Fbills over the colder winter months
OL,17,Fwhen consumption is higher."
OL,19,FThe tariff rise is below Jersey's
OL,20,Fcurrent rate of inflation, which is
OL,21,F2.8%.
